A father who had a tumour  weighing almost a stone on his face is having the last of the growth removed - ten years after it started growing.

Stefan Zoleik,  from Martin, Slovakia, became a social recluse as the fatty lump grew from ear to ear.

Doctors were unable to operate because of health complications. 

But in June last year the 47-year-old underwent a five-hour removal procedure.  

