Medics are now hoping additional surgery will get rid of all the affected cells.

The former plumber suffers from a rare condition called Madelung disease, which causes tumours to grow.

The problems started in his early 20s when he noticed he was developing a large jaw.

He said: 'Since the surgery last year my life has changed incredibly. I don't know why it wasn't possible for it to be done earlier but I'm just grateful that it has been done now.'

