Madelung disease is a rare condition that causes tumours to grow around the neck, shoulders and upper arms.

It usually affects men between the ages of 30 and 70. 

It can lead to a loss of neck mobility and pain.

The growths can also become cancerous in rare circumstances. Their exact cause is unknown.

One benefit of the operation is that it stopped people staring at him in the street. 

Mr Zoleik, a husband and father-of-two, said: 'I'll finally be able to go for a beer with friends without people turning their heads and pointing at me.

'My family were really surprised how well I looked when they came to visit me in the hospital after the operation.

'Over everything else it was my family who helped me the most. They supported me both before and after the surgery, and are my rock that also gave me the strength to recover.'

